- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper focuses on generating SQL queries for databases with multiple tables and complex queries. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new neural network architecture for the text-to-SQL task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses machine learning techniques to train and evaluate the proposed model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with retrieving information from databases using natural language queries.
